<br>
You say, &quot;Hide&quot;<br>
You say, &quot;Invis or FD if you can.&quot;<br>
<br>
A few seconds later the entire cabin clears through a sitting unbuffed raid in very short order.  Dust settles, the inkies walk back.<br>
<br>
Survivors are 4 rogues, 1 shadowknight, and 1 enchanter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uvinneecyberstabber.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Vinnee Cyberstabber</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/13/02 3:06:02 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=22771.topic&index=21>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Times when you love being a rogue</span><hr size=1> I was in the Lake of Ill Omen the other night after reaching my 16th Rank of Backstabbing.  I read most of the places to hunt at this level and decided that LOiO would be my best bet.<br>
<br>
I started out soloing then got a tell from this small group near me (druid &amp; warrior) if I would like to join them.  Seeing this as an opportunity to work on my backstab skill, I readily agreed.<br>
<br>
Druid buffed us up and the warrior started pulling.  For the first few pulls things went as well as they could be.  We killed the mobs but I felt things could be done differently.  All of a sudden, a cleric LFG comes along and we snagged her asap!<br>
<br>
I then said to the group &quot;Ok.. get ready, cause I'm gonna pull!&quot;<br>
<br>
The Warrior laughed, the cleric said &quot;huh?&quot; and the druid /gulped hard.<br>
<br>
WHAM!  I get sow and i'm off.  First pull was a Sarnak Conscript.  Pulled him back to the group and saw a tiger walking by.....pulled it.  Got back to the group and helped finish off the Sarnak and saw a gobbo battlemaster walking by... grabbed him too.<br>
<br>
I did this constantly for about 15 mins....  Cleric says &quot;I've got 40 mana&quot;.  I said &quot;Not any more!&quot;  Went and pulled more.  <br>
<br>
The group broke up about 2 hours later, after all of us had dinged into a new level.  This was the first group that actually thanked me for pulling and that they looked forward to grouping with me again!<br>
<br>
Little things like that and knowing the abilities of the other classes is what made my experience of being the rogue in this group the best.  <br>
<br>
Vinnee <br>
19th Rogue<br>
